-- Dexia Paid Bonuses to About 360 Workers in December, L’Echo Says
-- B y   A o i f e   W h i t e
-- 2012-01-06T07:15:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/dexia-paid-bonuses-to-about-360-workers-in-december-l-echo-says.html
Dexia SA (DEXB) , the French-Belgian lender
that is being broken up, paid bonuses to some 360 employees in
December, L’Echo  reported .  High-ranked staff received as much as much as 45,000 euros
($57,500) gross, while lower-level workers got payments of
between 2,500 euros and 5,000 euros, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aoife White in Brussels at 
 awhite62@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 